Program: Discovery
Title: Aggressive symbiosis
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwt1
Last Broadcast Date: 27 January 1997
A look at why viruses that do animals no harm are so dangerous to humans. A report on aggressive symbiosis, why viruses such as Aids and Ebola allow their monkey and ape hosts to survive but will kill humans because they post a threat to the viruses' first host. Also in the programme, a chemical cure for memory loss, why looking to the past could give us clues to the future and safe sun worship. Show less